---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Terms of Service - Kinu" description="Terms of Service for Kinu messaging application.">
  <nav class="fixed top-0 left-0 right-0 z-50 bg-white/80 backdrop-blur-lg border-b border-slate-200">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-4 flex items-center justify-between">
      <a href="/" class="flex items-center gap-3">
        <img src="/logo.png" alt="Kinu" class="h-10 w-auto" />
      </a>
      <div class="hidden md:flex items-center gap-6">
        <a href="/#features" class="text-slate-600 hover:text-slate-900 transition-colors text-sm">Features</a>
        <a href="/whitepaper" class="text-slate-600 hover:text-slate-900 transition-colors text-sm">Whitepaper</a>
        <a href="/#notify" class="bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded-lg text-sm font-medium transition-colors">
          Get Early Access
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </nav>

  <main class="pt-24 pb-16">
    <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6">
      <header class="mb-12">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4 text-slate-900">Terms of Service</h1>
        <p class="text-slate-500">Last updated: January 2025</p>
      </header>

      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none space-y-8">
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-slate-900">1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
          <p class="text-slate-600">
            By accessing or using Kinu ("the Service"), you agree to be bound by these Terms of Service.
            If you do not agree to these terms, do not use the Service.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-slate-900">2. Description of Service</h2>
          <p class="text-slate-600">
            Kinu is a privacy-focused messaging application that provides:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-slate-600 space-y-2 mt-4">
            <li>End-to-end encrypted messaging</li>
            <li>Bluetooth mesh networking capabilities</li>
            <li>Cloud-based message delivery via the Matrix protocol</li>
            <li>Hybrid transport for seamless communication</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-slate-900">3. User Accounts</h2>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 text-slate-800">3.1 Account Creation</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-600">
            To use Kinu, you must create an account. You agree to:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-slate-600 space-y-2 mt-4">
            <li>Provide accurate information during registration</li>
            <li>Maintain the security of your account credentials</li>
            <li>Notify us immediately of any unauthorized access</li>
            <li>Be responsible for all activities under your account</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 mt-6 text-slate-800">3.2 Account Security</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-600">
            Your encryption keys are stored on your device. If you lose access to your device without
            a backup, you may permanently lose access to your message history. Kinu cannot recover
            your encryption keys.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-slate-900">4. Acceptable Use</h2>
          <p class="text-slate-600">
            You agree NOT to use Kinu to:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-slate-600 space-y-2 mt-4">
            <li>Violate any applicable laws or regulations</li>
            <li>Harass, threaten, or abuse other users</li>
            <li>Distribute malware or malicious content</li>
            <li>Attempt to compromise the security of the Service</li>
            <li>Impersonate other users or entities</li>
            <li>Send spam or unsolicited messages</li>
            <li>Engage in any activity that disrupts the Service</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-slate-900">5. Privacy</h2>
          <p class="text-slate-600">
            Your use of Kinu is also governed by our <a href="/privacy" class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-700">Privacy Policy</a>,
            which describes how we collect, use, and protect your information.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-slate-900">6. Encryption and Content</h2>
          <p class="text-slate-600">
            Kinu provides end-to-end encryption for your messages. This means:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-slate-600 space-y-2 mt-4">
            <li>We cannot read, monitor, or moderate message contents</li>
            <li>You are solely responsible for the content you send</li>
            <li>We cannot recover deleted or lost messages</li>
            <li>Encryption does not exempt you from applicable laws</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-slate-900">7. Mesh Networking</h2>
          <p class="text-slate-600">
            When using mesh networking features:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-slate-600 space-y-2 mt-4">
            <li>Your device may relay messages for other users (encrypted, unreadable)</li>
            <li>You consent to your device being discoverable via Bluetooth when the feature is enabled</li>
            <li>Mesh networking performance depends on nearby Kinu users</li>
            <li>You may disable mesh networking at any time in settings</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-slate-900">8. Intellectual Property</h2>
          <p class="text-slate-600">
            The Kinu application, including its code, design, and documentation, is protected by
            intellectual property laws. The Kinu client is open source under the Apache 2.0 license.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-slate-900">9. Disclaimers</h2>
          <p class="text-slate-600">
            THE SERVICE IS PROVIDED "AS IS" WITHOUT WARRANTIES OF ANY KIND. WE DO NOT GUARANTEE:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-slate-600 space-y-2 mt-4">
            <li>Uninterrupted or error-free service</li>
            <li>That the service will meet your specific requirements</li>
            <li>The accuracy or reliability of any information</li>
            <li>That defects will be corrected</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-slate-900">10. Limitation of Liability</h2>
          <p class="text-slate-600">
            TO THE MAXIMUM EXTENT PERMITTED BY LAW, KINU SHALL NOT BE LIABLE FOR ANY INDIRECT,
            INCIDENTAL, SPECIAL, CONSEQUENTIAL, OR PUNITIVE DAMAGES, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO
            LOSS OF PROFITS, DATA, OR USE.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-slate-900">11. Termination</h2>
          <p class="text-slate-600">
            We may suspend or terminate your account if you violate these terms. You may delete
            your account at any time through the app settings. Upon termination, your right to
            use the Service ceases immediately.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-slate-900">12. Changes to Terms</h2>
          <p class="text-slate-600">
            We may modify these terms at any time. We will notify users of material changes via
            the app. Continued use after changes constitutes acceptance of the new terms.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-slate-900">13. Governing Law</h2>
          <p class="text-slate-600">
            These terms are governed by the laws of the State of California, United States,
            without regard to conflict of law principles.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-slate-900">14. Contact</h2>
          <p class="text-slate-600">
            For questions about these terms, contact us at:
            <a href="mailto:legal@kinuchat.com" class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-700">legal@kinuchat.com</a>
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>

  <footer class="border-t border-slate-200 py-8 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 text-center">
      <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm">
        &copy; 2026 Kinu Foundation. All rights reserved.
      </p>
    </div>
  </footer>
</Layout>
